<%= content_for :title do %>
  TrackExp | Privacy Policy
<% end %>

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-bg dark:text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
  
  <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Last updated: <%= Time.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>
    
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      At TrackExp, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. 
      This Privacy Policy explains how we handle any information we collect when you visit our website or use our services.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We collect minimal personal information.</strong> The only personal information we collect is what you explicitly provide when creating an account, such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Password (stored in encrypted form)</li>
      <li>Any financial information you choose to enter into the application</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>
      We use your personal information solely for the purpose of providing you with our expense tracking service:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>To create and manage your account</li>
      <li>To provide the core functionality of tracking expenses and income</li>
      <li>To communicate with you about your account or our services</li>
      <li>To improve our service based on anonymized usage patterns</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>
      All your financial data is stored securely in our database. We implement appropriate security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Analytics and Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use Cloudflare for traffic analytics and security purposes. Cloudflare may collect anonymous usage data such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP addresses (anonymized)</li>
      <li>Browser type</li>
      <li>Device information</li>
      <li>Pages visited</li>
      <li>Time and date of visits</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This information is used solely for analyzing traffic patterns, improving our website performance, and enhancing security. We do not use this data to personally identify individual users.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      Except for Cloudflare (used for traffic analytics and security), we do not share your data with any third-party services, advertisers, or marketing companies.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Your Data Rights</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal information</li>
      <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
      <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
      <li>Export your data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, please contact us through your account settings or via email.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@trackexp.com.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<%= content_for :footer do %>
  <%= render partial: 'shared/footer' %>
<% end %> 